This paper is about Android malware detection using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of multiple views and graph kernels, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a unified framework, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses multiple kernel learning, which is a technique commonly used in data science (cs.DS).
